item.description:
Well, I thought I would share some tricks I use for easy data CRUD&rsquo;s in C (potentially C++/ObjC but its lacking typesafety). I&rsquo;m using sqlite here, but could apply to any database.
This is how my data access works - I&rsquo;m not saying its the best approach, its just how its evolved for me.
/* The account table name */ #define ACCOUNT_TABLE &quot;account&quot; /* a structure representing the account fields */ field_map account_values[] = { {&quot;login&quot;, &amp;acc-&gt;login, SQL_TEXT}, {&quot;email&quot;, &amp;acc-&gt;email, SQL_TEXT}, {&quot;password&quot;, &amp;acc-&gt;password, SQL_TEXT}, {&quot;timezone&quot;, &amp;acc-&gt;timezone, SQL_INT}, {0} }; /* saves the fields to the database */ acc-&gt;id = db_save(account_values, ACCOUNT_TABLE, acc-&gt;id);  As you can see, saving a structure is as simple as creating a field_map table and calling db_save.
